                <h1>Mastodon: The Giant Prehistoric Mammal</h1>
                <p>Mastodons were large, elephant-like mammals that roamed North America and Eurasia during the Pleistocene Epoch. Known for their long, curved tusks and robust bodies, these fascinating creatures were herbivorous, primarily feeding on shrubs and trees. Fossil evidence suggests they thrived in diverse habitats until their extinction around 10,000 years ago.</p>
